SIMPLE: demilune
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Demilune
<hw>Dem"i*lune`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>demi-
lune</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Fort.)</fld> <def>A work
constructed beyond the main ditch of a fortress, and in front of the
curtain between two bastions, intended to defend the curtain; a ravelin.
See <er>Ravelin</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>A crescentic mass of granular
protoplasm present in the salivary glands.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Each crescent is made of polyhedral cells which under
some circumstances are supposed to give rise to new salivary
cells.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Demiman</ent>⟦br⟧
